<subSubSection id="FF0BE1DF7477262A9996789333395082" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="64D1018317A6DDF366280EDB84FBCBDE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EB8E1530657EC00E1A01F860C6FA93B7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Apparently endemic to Caatinga and Mata 
<normalizedToken id="7EA20A9C984F1C6E4A80AE5B2657AA12" originalValue="Atlântica">Atlantica</normalizedToken>
in Bahia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B4BD9F85974EDE766658FF4ACF6AC8ED" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="7E96BB585C01FA141CFB902D52E6D167" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">BRAZIL. Bahia</emphasis>
: Jussiape, ca. 14 km antes de Jussiape, na estrada de 
<normalizedToken id="7A2594921079FC7D0A5D0BBFE3A7DBEF" originalValue="Capão">Capao</normalizedToken>
da Volta, 
<emphasis id="6CEDB020E06386C2AB290F86C1786FA1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">R.M. Harley &amp; A.M. Giulietti 53949</emphasis>
(HUEFS, SP); 
<normalizedToken id="B6F5D7B928D731335C8A0351FFC80E3B" originalValue="Abaíra">Abaira</normalizedToken>
, 
<emphasis id="9917D660DC8D0C773049488F72E5A058" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">W. Ganev 3275</emphasis>
(HUEFS, HST); Boa Nova, P.N. de Boa Nova, 
<emphasis id="724D0A51A6ECB59D2675B3A67045DB6E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
G.S. 
<normalizedToken id="A3FC40519DC8E1C04C9C9FA094576AE1" originalValue="Brandão">Brandao</normalizedToken>
&amp; G.S. Silva
</emphasis>
335 (PEUFR); 
<normalizedToken id="7968F095A06F3A3347A46F5A79A76254" originalValue="Poções">Pocoes</normalizedToken>
, Morrinhos, 
<emphasis id="FB1FCD1522A926B98A3D18D612522553" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M.M. Saavedra</emphasis>
1007 (RB).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1BFB1F199C5E4FCF0E15613A7CFAF67F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="95DF10994D65C4522D47403ABA1B5EDD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9BABFF514B1E4A68E16CBBEED674F32B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Differs from 
<taxonomicName id="3792016B5C15A98F4DF96783FA148A7B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pintoi">
<emphasis id="BBB47ACF1D0ABEDB54BB8226ED3802AA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea pintoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only in the suburceolate corolla with exserted stamens. It is perhaps more widely distributed than is suggested here because of confusion with 
<taxonomicName id="3BAA9481AE9D78D058CCA3E19025F2FE" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pintoi">
<emphasis id="8E8AD2F611941F112AAB65CB7FC54BAC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea pintoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
